properties.boundary_description: (1) The beginning point is on the Long Mountain map on U.S. Highway 377 at the 1,748-foot elevation point, just east of Bench Mark 1678; (2) Proceed northwest in a straight line to the marked 1,705-foot elevation contour at the intersection of Big Bluff Creek and an unnamed, unpaved road; then (3) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the 1,800-foot elevation contour; then (4) Proceed easterly, then southeasterly, then northerly along the meandering 1,800-foot elevation contour to its intersection with an unnamed, unpaved road running perpendicular to the unnamed road known locally as Red Lane, northeast of the marked 1,844-foot elevation point; then (5) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the marked 1,866-foot elevation point; then (6) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the 1,900-foot elevation contour; then (7) Proceed southerly, then northeasterly along the meandering 1,900-foot elevation contour to its intersection with an unnamed, unpaved road southeast of the marked “Spring”; then (8) Proceed southeasterly, then easterly along the unnamed, unpaved road, passing another unnamed, unimproved road, to its intersection with a second unnamed, unpaved road south of the marked 1,908-foot elevation point; then (9) Proceed southwesterly along the second unnamed, unpaved road to its intersection with Honey Creek; then (10) Proceed southerly along Honey Creek to its intersection with State Highway 29; then (11) Proceed southeasterly along the westbound lane of State Highway 29 to its intersection with U.S. Highway 377; then (12) Proceed southeasterly along U.S. Highway 377 along the westbound lane to its intersection with U.S. Highway 87; then  (13) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the marked 1,648-foot elevation point at the intersection of State Highway 386 and an unnamed road known locally as Old Katemcy Mason Road; then (14) Proceed north along Old Katemcy Mason Road to the marked 1692-foot elevation point; then (15) Proceed northeast in a straight line past Little Willow Creek to the marked 1,842-foot elevation point; then (16) Proceed east-southeast in a straight line to the marked 1,693-foot elevation point on an unnamed, light-duty road known locally as Blackjack Road; then (17) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the marked 1,653-foot elevation point on an unnamed road known locally as Thomas Road; then (18) Proceed northeasterly in a straight line to the marked 1,629-foot elevation point at the intersection of two unnamed roads known locally as Spy Rock Road and Wagram Road; then (19) Proceed northeast in a straight line to Bench Mark 1,675 along State Highway 1222; then (20) Proceed northwest in a straight line, crossing over the shared Mason–McCulloch county line, to the marked 1,602-foot elevation point along an unnamed road known locally as State Highway 224; then (21) Proceed north in a straight line to the intersection of State Highway 734 and an unnamed road known locally as County Road 222; then (22) Proceed northwesterly along State Highway 734 to its intersection with an unnamed road known locally as Private Road 661; then (23) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the marked 1,613-foot elevation point; then (24) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the marked 1,625-foot elevation point; then (25) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the marked 1,610-foot elevation point along South Farm-to Market Road 1851; then (28) Proceed west-northwest along Old Katemcy Mason Road to its intersection with 1222, then (29) Proceed west-southwest along State Highway 1222 to its intersection with the 1700-foot contour line, then (30) Proceed southwest in a straight line crossing the 1750-foot contour to a fork in Dry Prong Katemcy Creek, north of the marked 1758 elevation point, then (31) Proceed southwesterly along Dry Prong Katemcy Creek to its intersection with an unnamed road known locally as Stark Road, also known locally as A H Road, then, (32) Proceed west, then northwest along Stark Road to the marked 2,037-foot elevation point; then (33) Proceed northwest in a straight line to the marked 1,971-foot elevation contour; then (34) Proceed north-northeast in a straight line to the marked 1,823-foot elevation contour; then (35) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the marked 1,770-foot elevation point along State Highway 1222; then (84) Proceed west in a straight line to the 1700-foot contour line; then (85) Proceed north in a straight line to the marked 1610-foot summit; then (86) Proceed west in a straight line to the marked 1801-foot summit; then (87) Proceed north in a straight line to the marked 1785-foot summit; then (88) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the marked 1728-foot summit; then (89) Proceed northwest in a straight line to the marked 1706-foot summit; then (90) Proceed east in a straight line to Honey Creek; then (91) Proceed north-easterly, then north-westerly, then north-easterly along Honey Creek to the marked 1727-foot elevation point at its intersection with State Highway 29; then (92) Proceed northwesterly along the eastbound lane of State Highway 29 to its intersection with U.S. Highway 377; then, (93) Proceed northwesterly along the eastbound lane of State Highway 29 to the marked 1737-foot elevation point; then, (94) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the marked 1762-foot elevation point; then (95) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the unmarked, unnamed road to the point where the road ends; then (96) Proceed southwesterly along the unmarked road to its intersection with US Highway 377; then (97) Proceed southeast in a straight line to the marked 1765-foot summit; then (98) Proceed southeast in a straight line to the end of the unmarked, unnamed road known locally as Lange Road; then (99) Proceed southwest in a straight line to the intersection of Big Bluff Creek and the unmarked, unnamed road known locally as Chimney Hollow Road; then (100) Proceed northwest in a straight line to the 1662-foot elevation point; then (101) Proceed northwest in a straight line to the marked 1794-foot elevation point; then (102) Proceed northeast in a straight line to the beginning point.
